verbs.description: [ARG1: DEMOCRATS in the U.S. Senate] , [V: joined] [ARG0: by three Republicans] , recently voted to reinstate “ net neutrality ” regulations imposed by the Obama administration in 2015 then later junked by the Trump administration . The proposal is unlikely to go anywhere in the House , and is mostly symbolic . But the debate was still illustrative , because it again highlighted the incoherence of net neutrality supporters ' arguments . Net neutrality regulations declare internet service providers ( ISPs ) to be public utilities subject to Title II of the federal Communications Act of 1934 , even though that law was designed to address phone monopolies and based on an even more antiquated 1887 law regulating railroads .
